fields.title: How to Train Your Dragon
fields.review: The story is so-so, but the animation is delicious.

fields.title: Top Gun: Maverick
fields.review: Tom Cruise is here to save cinema.

fields.title: Ready Player One
fields.review: It's pure entertainment, and gives Spielberg an easel to prop his sentimental painting on, and all the colors on his palette to do so.

fields.title: Thor: Love and Thunder
fields.review: The film passes through the nervous system without delivering any sustenance or even leaving a residue.

fields.title: La La Land
fields.review: The movie has charm, at least, if nothing else. And as an attempt to pay homage to a vanishing world, La La Land is as dutiful as it is endearing - sweet, if a little sour, too.

fields.title: Drifting Home
fields.review: There's enough liveliness to Drifting Home that two hours in a single location against a minimal background doesn't actually feel like overkill.

fields.title: Jumanji: The Next Level
fields.review: It's funny and diverting and it's even found accommodation for the elderly. Thoughtful, that, in a family film.

fields.title: Hatching
fields.review: This artful combination of horror film and pubescent trauma is distinguished by its insights into the world of its young teen heroine.

fields.title: Cruella
fields.review: Cruella is doing enough to be seductively fun and entertaining, at least for the first 90 minutes.
